  "designNotes": "The Developer template feels like a well-maintained README rendered as a personal page. JetBrains Mono dominates interactive and structural elements (hero, section titles, prompts, metrics) while Inter handles prose — the same cognitive split developers live in between editor and browser. The GitHub contribution heatmap is 364 static HTML divs with zero JS dependency for visuals, making it print-safe and instantly recognizable to technical reviewers. Terminal aesthetic is disciplined: traffic-light dots, '> ' prompts, '// ' prefixes, and '#' category markers appear only in structurally appropriate contexts."
